    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the fish is cooking, melt 40g <span class=\"text-purple\">[60g]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[80g]</span> <strong>butter</strong> in a pot over a low heat</p><p>Once melted, remove the pot from the heat and add your <strong>mayo</strong>, <strong>white wine vinegar</strong>,<strong> Dijon mustard </strong>and <strong>chopped dill</strong></p><p>Whisk until you have a thick sauce<strong> </strong>then season with<strong> salt </strong>and<strong> pepper </strong>–<strong> </strong>this is your <strong>speedy</strong> <strong>herby hollandaise</strong></p>",
